==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emphysema
<hw>Em`phy*se"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/ inflation, fr. <?/ to inflate; <?/ in + <?/ to blow: cf. F.
<ets>emphys⟦egrave⟧me</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A swelling
produced by gas or air diffused in the cellular tissue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Emphysema of the lungs</b></col>, <col><b>Pulmonary
emphysema</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a common disease of
the lungs in which the air cells are distended and their partition walls
ruptured by an abnormal pressure of the air contained in
them.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emphysematous</ent>⟦br⟧
